title: TREASURIES-U.S. yields hold at lower levels after U.S. PCE, jobless claims data
text:
data@
NEW YORK, March 29 (Reuters) - U.S. Treasury yields remained at lower levels on Thursday with the 10-year yield hovering at seven-week lows after in-line data on domestic personal spending in February and weekly jobless claims falling to a 45-year low.
At 8:51 a.m. (1251 GMT), the yield on 10-year Treasury notes was down 0.7 basis point at 2.768 percent. (Reporting by Richard Leong Editing by Nick Zieminski)
